What it Does
Extends script from v1, but now we're experimenting with deletion of values instead of adding them.

What it Demonstrates
.clear() empties a list
.remove(value) deletes the matching item
.pop(index) removes the item from the list based on its index value


Code

camping_list = ["tent", "sleeping bag", "coffee", "water", "smore kit", "grill", "knife", "Starlink", "snacks", "food"]

camp_site = ["Crystal Lake", 404, 89.3, 10, True]

camping_list.append("toilet paper")

camping_list.extend(["bidet", "flavored water"])

camping_list = camping_list + ["ATVs"]

camping_list.insert(0, "gas")

camping_list.insert(-1, "cutlery")

camp_site.clear()

camping_list.remove("tent")

camping_list.remove("sleeping bag")

print("This item was just deleted: " + camping_list.pop(4))

camping_list.pop(4)

print(camping_list)
